{"id": "stable-render-dir", "phase": "local", "level": "high", "decision": "Where does a session render its report before it's uploaded?", "choice": "Render <name>.html/.slides.html into a stable local STAGING dir data_root/viz (~/.claude/plugins/data/trainlint-trainlint/viz) instead of the versioned ROOT/viz -- one stable place the uploader reads from, unaffected by plugin version bumps. BUILT 2026-07-02 (cache): viz.generate outdir -> paths.data_root()/'viz'; all 5 existing projects regenerated there (10 files, spot-checked). RESIDUAL: cache-only, not yet shipped to source.", "principle": "stable-not-versioned-path", "status": "decided", "why": "outdir=ROOT/viz (viz.py:1556) is version-scoped; the uploader needs ONE stable local path to read the freshest report from, regardless of plugin version.", "match": "viz\\.py|outdir|ROOT ?/|data_root|generate\\(", "plain": "Render each report into one stable local folder the uploader can always find it in.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/.claude/plugins/data/trainlint-trainlint/viz", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/research/viz.py", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [3330, 3345], "commit": "514cf3d3ab51"}]}
{"id": "tenant-binding", "phase": "identity", "pillar": true, "load_bearing": true, "level": "high", "decision": "How do a machine upload (no browser) and a browser view (Access login) resolve to the SAME isolated tenant?", "choice": "On first browser login at secondfoundationlabs.com, the Worker reads the Access-verified email and mints a SIGNED upload token carrying that user's namespace; the installer pastes the token into the plugin. Uploads present the token -> Worker validates the signature -> stores under that namespace. Views present the Access JWT -> Worker derives the SAME namespace from the email. One binding, both directions. SCAFFOLDED 2026-07-02 (code on disk, NOT yet deployed/verified against Cloudflare).", "principle": "bind-machine-to-human-identity", "status": "decided", "why": "Access authenticates a BROWSER (gives the human email); a machine POST has no browser, so Access can't log it in. Without a token that ties the upload to the same email-derived namespace, uploads land wrong or tenants leak into each other.", "match": "token|namespace|Cf-Access|jwt|identity|tenant|sign|isolat", "plain": "Give each user one signed token so their plugin's uploads and their browser logins land in the same private space.", "not_this": "exposing reports via a cloudflared tunnel or an always-on host server instead of the Cloudflare Worker + R2 serverless service", "not_re": "cloudflared|tunnel route dns|systemd.*(http\\.server|serve)|--bind 0\\.0\\.0\\.0", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/report-server/worker/src/auth.js", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/report-server/worker/src/auth.js", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [36, 53], "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}, {"file": "hansard/report-server/worker/src/auth.js", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [130, 156], "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
{"id": "access-login", "phase": "identity", "level": "high", "decision": "Who is allowed to sign up and log in, and how?", "choice": "SUPERSEDED Cloudflare Access with worker-native Google OAuth (index.js /auth/google + callback, GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID/SECRET as worker secrets) + magic-link token pairing (/link). OPERATOR DECIDED 2026-07-08: OPEN registration — any Google account may log in, isolation is per-namespace; no allowlist. ADMIN_EMAILS may view all namespaces. Verified live: /auth/google 302s to accounts.google.com; anonymous visits get only the login shell.", "principle": "edge-auth-zero-trust", "status": "decided", "why": "the login for ALL tenants is handled once by Access -- no per-installer infra. Allowlist-first because you'll be STORING other people's project plans; open signup means anyone's plans land on your infra.", "match": "access|zero.?trust|policy|allowlist|google|github|identity provider|IdP", "plain": "Let each user log in with Google/GitHub via one Cloudflare Access rule; start invite-only.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/report-server/worker/src/index.js", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/report-server/worker/src/index.js", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [212, 247], "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
{"id": "serverless-store", "phase": "cloud", "pillar": true, "level": "high", "decision": "Where are the uploaded report HTMLs stored?", "choice": "Cloudflare R2 (object storage), key = <namespace>/<project>.html and <namespace>/<project>.slides.html. R2 over KV: reports are 25-105 KB blobs (measured), R2 is the blob store and is cheap/S3-like; KV is for small hot values. One bucket, namespaced by tenant. SCAFFOLDED 2026-07-02 (code on disk, NOT yet deployed/verified against Cloudflare).", "principle": "object-store-for-blobs", "status": "decided", "why": "the reports are static HTML blobs; R2 stores + serves them via the Worker with per-key access, and namespacing the key by tenant is the isolation boundary.", "match": "R2|KV|bucket|wrangler|storage|put\\(|get\\(", "plain": "Store each user's report files in a Cloudflare R2 bucket under their own namespace.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/report-server/worker/wrangler.toml", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/report-server/worker/wrangler.toml", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
{"id": "worker-serve", "phase": "cloud", "level": "high", "decision": "What does the Worker actually expose?", "choice": "A Cloudflare Worker with three routes, ALL scoped to the caller's namespace: POST /api/upload (token-auth, writes <ns>/<project>.html to R2), GET / (index of the caller's own reports), GET /<project>.html (streams the caller's report from R2, 404 if not theirs). Access protects the GET routes; the token protects upload. SCAFFOLDED 2026-07-02 (code on disk, NOT yet deployed/verified against Cloudflare).", "principle": "one-worker-scoped-to-caller", "status": "decided", "why": "a single Worker is the whole server side -- upload sink, index, and per-report serve -- and every route derives the namespace from the caller so cross-tenant reads are impossible by construction.", "match": "worker|fetch\\(|/api/upload|index|route|request\\.", "plain": "One Cloudflare Worker handles upload, the per-user index, and serving each report -- always scoped to who's calling.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/report-server/worker/src/index.js", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/report-server/worker/src/index.js", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [67, 85], "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
{"id": "worker-route", "phase": "cloud", "level": "impl", "decision": "How does secondfoundationlabs.com reach the Worker?", "choice": "Apex custom_domain route: secondfoundationlabs.com binds straight to the worker (wrangler.toml routes). Verified live: site serves the login shell on the apex.", "principle": "worker-custom-domain", "status": "decided", "why": "DNS is already on Cloudflare, so binding the apex domain straight to the Worker is the least-setup routing.", "match": "route|custom domain|workers\\.dev|wrangler.*domain|secondfoundationlabs", "plain": "Point the domain straight at the Worker with Cloudflare's custom-domain binding.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/report-server/worker/wrangler.toml", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/report-server/worker/wrangler.toml", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [15, 18], "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
{"id": "plugin-upload", "phase": "upload", "pillar": true, "level": "high", "decision": "How does an installer's plugin push its rendered report to the cloud, without disturbing non-hosted users?", "choice": "A new plugin step (research/push.py) that, AFTER viz.generate, POSTs the report + slides HTML to https://secondfoundationlabs.com/api/upload with the installer's token from config (env TRAINLINT_REPORT_TOKEN or a config file). FAIL-SILENT when no token is set -- so installers who don't opt in are completely unaffected. Hooked into the close alongside the existing HTML/SLIDES sign-off. CONFIRMED LIVE 2026-07-08: viz.generate auto-calls push.push_report (fail-silent); explicit re-upload of report+slides returned 200; anonymous token auto-minted at data_root/.token; magic-link pairing printed on first upload.", "principle": "opt-in-fail-silent-upload", "status": "decided", "why": "reports are generated on the installer's machine; the only way to a hosted view is to upload. Opt-in + fail-silent keeps the plugin's existing local behavior intact for anyone who doesn't configure a token.", "match": "push\\.py|upload|POST|TRAINLINT_REPORT_TOKEN|requests\\.|urllib|curl", "plain": "Add an opt-in step that uploads each rendered report to the service, silent for anyone without a token.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/research/push.py", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/research/push.py", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [43, 85], "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
{"id": "onboarding", "phase": "upload", "level": "impl", "decision": "How does an installer get their token into the plugin, once?", "choice": "Zero-config: first report upload auto-mints a local anonymous token (data_root/.token) and prints a one-click magic link (server/link?token=...); the installer opens it, logs in with Google once, and the token pairs to their account. Verified live 2026-07-08: /link 200, ?token= magic login 302.", "principle": "copy-one-token-onboarding", "status": "decided", "why": "the lightest per-installer setup is a single copy-paste of a token surfaced right on their logged-in page.", "match": "README|onboard|TRAINLINT_REPORT_TOKEN|config|token page", "plain": "Onboarding is: log in once, copy the token shown, paste it into the plugin.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/research/push.py", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/research/push.py", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "lines": [76, 83], "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
{"id": "verify-isolation", "phase": "verify", "level": "impl", "decision": "How do we PROVE one tenant cannot see another's reports?", "choice": "PARTIAL 2026-07-08: token-layer isolation PROVEN live 8/8 (verify_isolation.py) — same-named cross-upload stays namespaced, zero cross-reads, admin route refuses non-admins. NOT yet covered (operator ruled: gate stays open until closed): two real Google-account tenants (needs operator+cz logins), /api/share->/accept consent flow, AgentHub relay paths, and a 503 (not 404) on one cross-read that needs explaining.", "principle": "prove-the-isolation-boundary", "status": "decided", "why": "multi-tenant with others' private plans -- a single cross-tenant read is the catastrophe; isolation must be TESTED, not assumed.", "match": "test|isolat|cross.?tenant|403|404|two token", "plain": "Prove with a test that user A can never reach user B's reports.", "artifact": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint/hansard/report-server/verify_isolation.py", "anchors": [{"file": "hansard/report-server/verify_isolation.py", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}, {"file": "hansard/report-server/TWO_ACCOUNT_TEST.md", "repo": "/home/shiyil/Trainlint", "commit": "e5e29fdc1d17"}]}
